Title: Safety Standards and Protection Against Child Sexual Abuse and Exploitation (CSAE)

Content:

At Bashiti HR, we are committed to ensuring the safety and protection of all users. Our applications strictly prohibit any form of child sexual abuse material (CSAM), exploitation, grooming, trafficking, or any behavior that endangers children.

We comply with international laws and industry standards related to CSAE, and we apply the following safeguards:

Zero-Tolerance Policy
We strictly prohibit the creation, distribution, sharing, or promotion of CSAM or any content involving the exploitation or endangerment of minors.

Proactive Monitoring
Our systems and internal review processes monitor for prohibited content and abusive behavior within legal and operational limits.

Reporting and Enforcement
Any detected or reported CSAE-related content or activity will result in immediate account suspension or termination.
We promptly report violations to relevant authorities and organizations such as NCMEC (National Center for Missing and Exploited Children) when applicable.

User Safety Measures
We implement technical and administrative safeguards to prevent misuse of our platform, including restricted uploads, activity monitoring, and secure user verification where required.

Compliance
We comply with local and international child protection laws and follow Google Playâ€™s CSAE policies.
